nodes.text: "The End of History" is a canon short story which is included in Star Wars Insider 154. It is written by Alexander Freed and is illustrated by Chris Scalf.
Alexander Freed, the author of "The End of History," said that the short story likely takes place around 10 BBY. However, this information is not officially established as canon.

When Miru Nadrinakar, a member of the Corellian Resistance, crashes on a Geonosian colony world, Antron Bach, an antique dealer in-hiding, must decide whether to help her escape the Galactic Empire or to protect the Jedi artifacts he has kept safe since the Jedi Order's destruction.
